Kibera Black Stars collected a comfortable 2-0 win over Mombasa Elite in an action-packed National Super League thriller at Camp Toyoyo on Sunday. Samuel Kapen was the toast for the Nairobi-based side, finding the back of the net on either side of the interval. Kapen broke the deadlock barely 10 minutes into play before returning to haunt the opponents with a 77th-minute superb strike. Mombasa Elite threw away a perfect opportunity to restore parity earlier in the game after squandering a penalty. The outcome fired Kibera to the seventh spot on the log with three rounds left to play. Former Kenyan Premier League sides, Kisumu All Stars and Vihiga United battled to a two-all draw at Moi Stadium, Kisumu. The outcome leaves Kisumu All Stars 15th on the log with 32 points while Vihiga United remain 11th with 41 points. Salim Muya emerged from the bench to net the only goal that fired Murang’a Seal to a crucial 1-0 win over Silibwet Leons at St. Sebastian Park. The victory left Murang’a Seal third on the log in the title contention bracket. Muhoroni Youth walloped Gusii FC 3-0 at Muhoroni Stadium to dislodge Shabana from the fourth spot, effectively reigniting their hopes for top-flight promotion. Mwatate United beat Shabana 3-2 at Wundanyi Stadium. Mwatate's Elly Saenyi bagged a brace to take command of the top scorers' standings with 21 goals. SS Assad and APS Bomet settled for a barren draw at Shamu Grounds. MCF suffered a 2-0 defeat to Mara Sugar at the Kericho Green Stadium. Coastal Heroes pipped Migori Youth 2-1 at the Serani Sports Grounds.